    <centralBlocks>
      <Value><![CDATA[[
  {
    "key": "78a9383e-7004-45b0-af38-cfc2d07ab02a",
    "name": "Why participate in GIVE?",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Why participate in GIVE?",
    "content": "<p><span class=\"lead\">The GIVE scheme offers you the opportunity to:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Build your skills, employability, and develop yourself personally and professionally.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Give back to Queen Margaret University.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Prepare yourself for a range of non-executive director roles.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"
  },
  {
    "key": "ed1875e4-6c60-48a6-bd69-cf4847ccf57f",
    "name": "Testimonials",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Testimonials",
    "content": "<?UMBRACO_MACRO macroAlias=\"Quote\" text=\"As a university committed to inclusiveness, we want our governing body to reflect the rich diversity of the groups we serve, and to hear the voices of people of all ages, backgrounds and circumstances. The GIVE programme will strengthen our ability to do that, along with providing a meaningful way for alumni to help shape QMU.\" source=\"Pamela Woodburn\" sourceExtra=\"Chair of the Court of Queen Margaret University\" />\n<p><img src=\"?mode=crop&amp;width=800\" alt=\"Pamela Woodburn\" width=\"800\" height=\"386.86296715741787\" data-udi=\"umb://media/0dc1542240e04d7aab71a8fbaea2efae\"></p>\n<?UMBRACO_MACRO macroAlias=\"Quote\" text=\"As Student President at QMU, I am a member of the University’s Court. Through my membership, I’ve witnessed the crucial role of the Court in contributing to the strategic direction of the University and ensuring good governance. The experience I’ve gained in being on the board has given me fantastic transferable skills, helping me to understand how businesses work, and how to work effectively with different boards and their members. Through this, my membership has given me an appetite for trustee and non-exec director roles in the future. By participating in GIVE, you can gain the same sort of benefits as I did from my role in the University Court and have the same sort of fulfilling experience as I have.\" source=\"\" sourceExtra=\"\" />\n<?UMBRACO_MACRO macroAlias=\"Quote\" text=\"Boards exist to guarantee positive and effective governance of organisations, making it so important that their membership reflects the diversity of our society, ensuring that a wide range of voices are heard, and that the decisions made benefit people from all different walks of life. As the GIVE scheme is designed to diversify the pool of candidates for QMU’s governing body, its Court, it serves as a great way to ensure that University governance addresses the needs of the communities it serves.\" source=\"Jay Brown\" sourceExtra=\"QMU Student President and Court Member\" />\n<p><img src=\"?mode=crop&amp;width=800\" alt=\"Jay Brown\" width=\"800\" height=\"386.86296715741787\" data-udi=\"umb://media/81dc7f667dde443b87c09b7834faa527\"></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "061888f7-ebcb-4bf3-8186-3caef4cd6a09",
    "name": "Details of the scheme",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Details of the scheme",
    "content": "<p><img src=\"?mode=crop&amp;width=800\" alt=\"Student Session at QMU\" width=\"800\" height=\"266.6666666666667\" data-udi=\"umb://media/7cf4304934ed4254b01247d9f74543b5\"></p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\">Details of the scheme</span></p>\n<p>Participants in the GIVE scheme will receive training and mentoring on board membership and will be able to observe meetings of the Court over the course of the 2024/5 academic year. (There are five meetings of Court held each academic year, normally held from 3pm on Wednesday afternoons.) Participants will also have the chance to observe meetings of Court sub-committees, including the Finance &amp; Estates Committee and the Audit and Risk Committee.  </p>\n<p>Mentoring will be from a current Court member and QMU staff who are experts in higher education (HE) governance. Training will include options to participate in external training programmes, e.g. through Advance HE.</p>\n<p>Participation in the Give scheme is voluntary, participants will not be remunerated, and the role is not eligible for visa sponsorship.</p>\n<p>GIVE scheme participants are not Court members and are therefore not expected to contribute to discussions or to take decisions. Following successful completion of the GIVE scheme, it is anticipated that participants will be eligible for full membership of the University Court and can join the Court subject to there being an appropriate vacancy in the membership.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "5aa917e8-7721-448e-a87a-bcee7ddacdf2",
    "name": "How to apply and key dates",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "How to apply and key dates",
    "content": "<p><span class=\"lead\">How to apply</span></p>\n<p>We are currently accepting applications for the 2024/2025 academic year. Applicants should be alumni of the University.</p>\n<p>To apply, please email <a href=\"mailto:give@qmu.ac.uk\" title=\"Contact: give@qmu.ac.uk\">give@qmu.ac.uk</a> with a copy of your CV and a covering letter setting out why the GIVE scheme interests you and why you think you are ready to be a board apprentice. The covering letter should be no more than one page.</p>\n<p>We recognise the value that a diversity of perspectives and lived experiences brings to Court, and we therefore welcome and encourage applications from underrepresented groups and those who have lived experiences of social inequalities.</p>\n<p><strong>The closing date for applications is 1 July 2024.</strong></p>\n<p>There are limited places available, and the Court's Nominations Committee will review applications over the summer. Applicants will be advised by the end of September with the scheme beginning in October.</p>\n<p>We welcome informal enquiries about applying. Please send any enquiries to <a href=\"mailto:give@qmu.ac.uk\" title=\"Contact: give@qmu.ac.uk\">give@qmu.ac.uk</a>.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "e3600de5-ec7b-4bd6-8059-d98a485725eb",
    "name": "The role of the University Court",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "The role of the University Court",
    "content": "<p>The Court is the governing body of the University.</p>\n<p>The University is a company limited by guarantee and a charity. Court members are consequently Directors and Charitable Trustees.</p>\n<p>The Court is responsible for carrying out the objectives of the University, ensuring the financial sustainability of the University and approving the strategic plan.</p>\n<p>The Court is supported by the following 'standing committees' i.e. the Finance &amp; Estates Committee, the Audit and Risk Committee, the Nominations Committee and the Senior Management Remuneration Committee. The Health and Safety Committee and the Equality and Diversity Committee also report to Court.</p>\n<p>The Court delegates responsibility to the Senate for the academic work of the University and the conferring of degrees and other awards. Operational management is delegated to the University’s senior leadership team under the leadership of the Principal and Vice-Chancellor.</p>\n<p>An important aspect of the Court’s work is establishing and monitoring systems of control and accountability, including financial control, and reviewing the performance of the University. The Court approves the mission and strategic vision of the University, its long-term business plans, key performance indicators (KPIs) and annual budgets, and ensures that these meet the needs of stakeholders.</p>\n<p>The Court also appoints the Principal of the University and has in place arrangements for monitoring their performance.</p>\n<p><br />Find out more about the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/2e8f8dd13ab94a76b4bf4560db43e92a}\" title=\"University Court\">University Court</a> and its <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/c69dfb00ccc947b48360bbab8f2ca385}\" title=\"Court\">current members</a>.</p>"
  }
]]]></Value>
